For debugging: Go into the "Get Info" contextual menu of your (test) executable (inside the "Executables" group in the left panel of XCode). Then go in the "Arguments" tab. You can add the following environment variables: Default: Set to: NSDebugEnabled NO "YES" NSZombieEnabled NO "YES" NSDeallocateZombies NO "YES" NSHangOnUncaughtException NO "YES" NSEnableAutoreleasePool YES "NO" NSAutoreleaseFreedObjectCheckEnabled NO "YES" NSAutoreleaseHighWaterMark 0 non-negative integer NSAutoreleaseHighWaterResolution 0 non-negative integer For info on these varaiables see NSDebug.h; http://theshadow.uw.hu/iPhoneSDKdoc/Foundation.framework/NSDebug.h.html For malloc debugging see: http://developer.apple.com/mac/library/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/ManagingMemory/Articles/MallocDebug.html
